<item>
            <title>[LU-9997] Suspicious assert check in ldlm_cli_cancel</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9997</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The assert in &lt;tt&gt;ldlm_cli_cancel()&lt;/tt&gt; seems to be problematic:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        /* Even &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; the lock is marked as LDLM_FL_BL_AST, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; is a LDLM_CANCEL  
         * RPC which goes to canceld portal, so we can cancel other LRU locks   
         * here and send them all as one LDLM_CANCEL RPC. */                    
        LASSERT(list_empty(&amp;amp;lock-&amp;gt;l_bl_ast));                                   
        list_add(&amp;amp;lock-&amp;gt;l_bl_ast, &amp;amp;cancels);  
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;because the lock may have been picked up LRU and added into canceling list.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
